                "a": "A muted, grounded green is the strongest single choice — sage, olive, or deep forest. Green sits in the easiest part of the spectrum for eyes to process over long stretches and reads as calm-but-alert thanks to its biophilic, nature-signaling effect. Keep it low in saturation (something earthy or slightly gray, not a bright kelly green) so it's restful at full-wall scale, and add a small warm accent — wood, brass, a touch of rust — so the room stays human rather than cold."
